# =================================================================
# fttmr: Faraday FTTMR010 Timer
# The Faraday timer provides three independent sets of sub-timers. Each
# sub-timer can use the internal system clock (PCLK) or external clock
# (EXTCLK) to increase or decrease counting. Two match registers are
# provided for each sub-timer. When the values of the match registers
# equal to any value of the sub-timers, the timer interrupt will be
# immediately triggered. Issuing a timer interrupt is decided by the
# register setting when an overflow occurs.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# fttmr TM1COUNTER: Timer 1 Count Register
# Holds the count value for timer 1. If the timer is not enabled the
# count will be held.
# Access RW
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
